Reasoning: The paper discusses the theoretical analysis of the $k$-means algorithm, which is a popular clustering heuristic used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, since the paper also discusses the quality of approximation and extensions of the basic $k$-means method, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
